We at Coforge are hiring for a Business Analyst - Financial position with the following skill set.&lt;hr&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Own the monthly IT financial reporting cycle, producing variance analysis across all OpEx and CapEx line items by pillar and project&lt;br&gt;• Monitor and flag over- and underspend trends through rolling forecasts and budget tracking&lt;br&gt;• Build and maintain financial views across IT pillars and project portfolios&lt;br&gt;• Track project-level financial performance against approved budgets and business cases&lt;br&gt;• Support investment decision-making by preparing financial impact summaries&lt;br&gt;• Develop dashboards and reporting tools to provide visibility into financial performance and trends&lt;br&gt;• Partner with Finance, Procurement, and IT teams to ensure accurate financial data and cost allocation&lt;br&gt;• Conduct vendor financial analysis, including spend tracking and benchmarking&lt;br&gt;• Identify and resolve data quality issues within financial systems&lt;br&gt;• Support strategic financial analysis (cost optimization, vendor consolidation, build vs. buy decisions)&lt;br&gt;• Document financial processes, templates, and reporting frameworks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• +5 years of experience in IT financial analysis, FP&amp;amp;A, or financial-focused business analysis&lt;br&gt;• Strong experience in budgeting, forecasting, and variance analysis (OpEx &amp;amp; CapEx)&lt;br&gt;• Proven ability to translate financial data into clear, actionable insights for leadership&lt;br&gt;• Advanced Excel skills (financial modeling, pivot tables, data analysis)&lt;br&gt;• Experience working with cross-functional teams (Finance, IT, Procurement)&lt;br&gt;• Strong communication and stakeholder management skills&lt;br&gt;• Experience in financial reporting and dashboard creation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience in IT or technology financial environments&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with ERP systems such as SAP, Oracle, or similar&lt;br&gt;• Experience with BI tools (Power BI, Tableau, or similar)&lt;br&gt;• Exposure to vendor financial analysis or commercial evaluation&lt;br&gt;• Understanding of IT project lifecycle and capital vs operating expense treatment&lt;br&gt;• Experience in professional services or consulting environments&lt;/p&gt;
